cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper introduces a collaborative autonomous mobile service robot based on the Beam telepresence system, which involves robotics technology. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper focuses on enhancing the telepresence system to improve human awareness and enable the robot to perform service tasks, which involves human-robot interaction. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions the increased computation and sensing capabilities of the robot, which suggests the use of AI techniques. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper mentions the robot's ability to perform target search and object delivery tasks, which suggests the use of computer vision techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper mentions the integration of the Beam with the Robot Operating System (ROS) framework, which involves system integration and control.
